## Design System UX (Single Source of Truth)

This file defines the **prescriptive** UX rules for the entire app (styles, typography, layout, states, and component patterns).

Goal: maintain a “dense, organized, power-user friendly” consistency (inspired by Linear / Airtable).

---

## 1. Colors & Theme (tokens)

The UI theme is driven by CSS variables (OKLCH) and used via Tailwind/Shadcn:

- Base container: `bg-background text-foreground`
- Card: `bg-card text-card-foreground`
- Accent: `bg-accent text-accent-foreground`
- Primary/Secondary: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`, `bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground`
- Border/Input/Ring: `border-border`, `ring`, `bg-input`

Main tokens (light mode, defined in `app/globals.css`):

- `--background`: oklch(0.985 0 0)
- `--foreground`: oklch(0.15 0 0)
- `--primary`: oklch(0.7141 0.1918 48.92)
- `--secondary`: oklch(0.94 0 0)
- `--muted`: oklch(0.96 0 0)
- `--accent`: oklch(0.95 0 0)
- `--destructive`: oklch(0.55 0.22 27)
- `--border`: oklch(0.91 0 0)
- `--ring`: oklch(0.7141 0.1918 48.92)

Dark mode:

- `.dark` redefines the same tokens (goal: contrast and readability, not just inversion).

Charts / graphs:

- `--chart-1` to `--chart-5` are dedicated colors for visualizations.

---

## 2. Fonts & Typography (utilities)

Fonts used:

- Body: `font-sans` (defined in code via Next/font + `--font-inter`)
- Display: via the `font-display` utility
  - The `font-display` utility is defined in `app/globals.css` and uses `--font-geist`

Reminder: in practice, follow the typography hierarchy described in section 6.

---

## 3. Layout primitives (Dashboard)

| Context | Pattern |
|---|---|
| Page container | `<div className="space-y-4 p-6 lg:p-8">` |
| Page title | Always `PageHeader` (`title` + optional `subtitle` + optional `action`) |
| Content sections (data, lists) | `SectionCard` (flat, thin border, no shadow) |
| Settings / account pages | 2-column layout: left nav (`w-48 shrink-0`) + right content inside `SectionCard` |
| KPI metrics strip | `StatCard` in `grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` |

---

## 4. Dashboard Constraints (components)

❌ **Never** use the shadcn `<Card>` (shadow + `CardHeader/CardContent`) in dashboard pages.

➡️ In `/dashboard`, use only `SectionCard` (flat style aligned with the design system).

---

## 5. Lists & Tables — 2 distinct patterns

### Pattern A — Rich card list (no headers)

Use when each item is a “standalone content block” (no need for aligned multi-column table).

- Container: `<ul className="space-y-3">` directly in the page (no `SectionCard` wrapper)
- Item: `<RichListItem>` (default class: `border border-border bg-card p-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-accent/40`)
- Pagination: `flex items-center justify-between` block below the list (simple, no table)

### Pattern B — Data table (with headers)

Use when data is structured in columns.

- Container: `<SectionCard noPadding>` wrapping the `<table>`
- `<th>`: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground`
- Header row: `bg-muted/60 border-b border-border`
- `<tr>`: `hover:bg-accent/60`, **no `divide-y`**, no `border-b` on rows
- Pagination: footer via the `footer` prop of `SectionCard`

❌ **Never mix both**

- No `<RichListItem>` inside a `SectionCard`
- No raw `<table>` without `SectionCard` wrapper

---

## 6. States (Empty / Loading)

- Zero-data: always `EmptyState`
- Loading:
  - list: `LoadingRows`
  - grid: `LoadingGrid`
- Do not render `null` conditionally without a placeholder.

---

## 7. Badges & Status

- Role/status indicators: always `StatusBadge`
- Do not use inline `Badge` with hardcoded colors scattered across pages
- Color mapping (if needed) should stay local to the page (e.g. a `roleColors` object), not inside shared components

---

## 8. Typography hierarchy (concrete rules)

- Page titles: `font-display text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight` (Geist)
- Section titles: `text-sm font-semibold text-foreground` (Inter)
- Labels / column headers: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground`
- Body: `text-sm text-foreground`
- Muted: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`

---

## 9. Branding (dynamic “public org” colors)

On public pages (`/org/[slug]`, preview, offers), colors come from the organization branding:

- `primaryColor`: `branding.primary_color` with fallback `#e07b39`
- `secondaryColor`: `branding.secondary_color` with fallback `#111827`

When adding brand-driven UI, ensure:
- readability (compute onPrimary/onSecondary)
- controlled transparency (e.g. `${primaryColor}14`, `${primaryColor}1a`, etc.)

